SIMPLE: utter
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Utter
<hw>Ut"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>utter</ets>,
originally the same word as <ets>outer</ets>. See <er>Out</er>, and cf.
<er>Outer</er>, <er>Utmost</er>.]</ety> ⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Outer.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Thine <xex>utter</xex>
eyen.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Chaucer.</au> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧By him a shirt
and <xex>utter</xex> mantle laid.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Chapman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As doth an hidden moth⟦br⟧
The inner garment fret, not th' <qex>utter</qex> touch.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Situated on the outside, or extreme limit; remote
from the center; outer.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Through <qex>utter</qex> and through middle darkness borne.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The very <qex>utter</qex> part of Saint Adelmes point is five
miles from Sandwich.</q> <rj><qau>Holinshed.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Complete; perfect; total; entire; absolute; <as>as,
<ex>utter</ex> ruin; <ex>utter</ex> darkness</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They . . . are <qex>utter</qex> strangers to all those anxious
thoughts which disquiet mankind.</q> <rj><qau>Atterbury.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Peremptory; unconditional; unqualified; final;
<as>as, an <ex>utter</ex> refusal or denial</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Clarendon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Utter bar</b></col> <fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>the whole body
of junior barristers.</cd> See <cref>Outer bar</cref>, under 1st
<er>Outer</er>. <mark>[Eng.]</mark> -- <col><b>Utter barrister</b></col>
<fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd>one recently admitted as barrister, who is
accustomed to plead without, or outside, the bar, as distinguished from
the <xex>benchers</xex>, who are sometimes permitted to plead within the
bar.</cd> <mark>[Eng.]</mark> <rj><au>Cowell.</au></rj> </cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Utter</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Utter
<hw>Ut"ter</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Uttered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Uttering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>outren</ets>, freq. of
<ets>outen</ets> to utter, put out, AS. <ets>⟦umac⟧tian</ets> to put
out, eject, fr. <ets>⟦umac⟧t</ets> out. ⟦root⟧198. See <er>Out</er>, and
cf. <er>Utter</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To put forth or out; to reach out.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How bragly [proudly] it begins to bud,⟦br⟧
And <qex>utter</qex> his tender head.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To dispose of in trade; to sell or vend.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Such mortal drugs I have, but Mantua's law⟦br⟧
Is death to any he that <qex>utters</qex> them.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They bring it home, and <qex>utter</qex> it commonly by the name
of Newfoundland fish.</q> <rj><qau>Abp. Abbot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>hence, to put in circulation, as money; to put off,
as currency; to cause to pass in trade; -- often used, specifically, of
the issue of counterfeit notes or coins, forged or fraudulent documents,
and the like; <as>as, to <ex>utter</ex> coin or bank
notes</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The whole kingdom should continue in a firm resolution never to
receive or <qex>utter</qex> this fatal coin.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To give public expression to; to disclose; to
publish; to speak; to pronounce.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Sweet as from blest,
<xex>uttering</xex> joy.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The words I <qex>utter</qex>⟦br⟧
Let none think flattery, for they 'll find 'em truth.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And the last words he <qex>uttered</qex> called me cruel.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To deliver; give forth; issue; liberate;
discharge; pronounce. See <er>Deliver</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Utterable</ent>⟦br⟧
